{
  "title": "Username & Password",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "DSP supports the Username & Password authentication flow."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "This method uses:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ul",
      "children": [
        { "type": "p", "content": "<strong>Username</strong>" },
        { "type": "p", "content": "<strong>Password + Security Token</strong>" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Authentication is handled securely through <strong>Salesforce's Named Credential</strong> feature, which stores and manages the credentials safely within the platform."
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Configure Username & Password Authentication"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Complete the steps below to configure Username & Password authentication between the Connect Org and the DSP App Org."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "1. Create a Named Credential in the DSP App Org",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "image",
          "content": "image/connection/username-password/named-credential-new-legacy.png",
          "alt": "Create Named Credential"
        },
        {
          "type": "instruction",
          "steps": [
            "<strong>URL</strong>: Use \"https://test.salesforce.com\" for sandbox environment or \"https://login.salesforce.com\" for production.",
            "<strong>Identity Type</strong>: Select Named Principal.",
            "<strong>Authentication Protocol</strong>: Choose Password Authentication",
            "<strong>Username</strong>: Enter the main username of the connected organization.",
            "<strong>Password</strong>: Enter the user's password combined with the security token. If a security token is not applicable, omit it."
          ],
          "content": "image/connection/username-password/named-credential-setup.png",
          "alt": "Named Credential Configurations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "2. Create a DSP Connection in the DSP App Org",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "image",
          "content": "image/connection/username-password/create-connection.png",
          "alt": "Create Connection"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "3. Test Connection",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "image",
          "content": "image/connection/username-password/test-connection.png",
          "alt": "Test Connection"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": "Prefer a walkthrough? Watch the complete setup demonstration below."
    },
    {
      "type": "video",
      "src": "https://youtu.be/cXwt1d7hkVU"
    }
  ]
}
